---
import MainLayout from "@/components/layout/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Read the Small Web Apps privacy overview and how browser-first tools are positioned in v1."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <section class="section-shell pt-12">
    <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
    <h1 class="mt-4 section-title">A browser-first privacy posture, explained plainly</h1>
    <div class="mt-8 card-surface rounded-[2rem] p-7 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-600 md:text-base">
      <p>
        Small Web Apps focuses on lightweight browser-based utilities. When a tool processes data locally in the browser, the app page should say so clearly.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        This privacy page is a site-level overview, not a blanket claim that every future tool behaves identically. Each app page remains responsible for accurately describing its own data handling.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        Users should avoid assuming that privacy behavior is identical across all future utilities. The page-level copy is the source of truth for each tool.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

